claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table presenting pre- and post-vaccination (day 0 and day 28) geometric mean antibody titers (with 95% CIs) and percentage response rates to three influenza vaccine antigens (A/Solomon Island/3/2006 H1N1, A/Wisconsin/67/2005 H3N2, B/Malaysia/2506/2004) across four groups: placebo, FluBlok, FluBlok PV, and FluBlok NPV. does not support the claim: the table provides immunogenicity and response rate data but contains no information on vaccine production methods, mutations arising during production, or their impact on effectiveness. Note: The snippet is clear and focused solely on antibody titers and response rates; no details on production-induced mutations are visible.
